00:29:59.044 --> 00:30:02.704
just one of the three BAF/SWI/SNF

502
00:30:02.744 --> 00:30:06.184
chromatin remodeling complexes, namely non-canonical BAF.

503
00:30:06.804 --> 00:30:10.704
BRD9 expression is elevated in AML,

504
00:30:10.723 --> 00:30:14.424
and SMARCB1, which is a component of the other two BAF

505
00:30:14.504 --> 00:30:15.294
complexes,

506
00:30:16.464 --> 00:30:20.204
is downregulated in AML blasts, suggesting perhaps a greater dependence

507
00:30:20.284 --> 00:30:22.844
on non-canonical BAF in AML blasts.

508
00:30:23.824 --> 00:30:27.544
Now, what is known is a number of groups have shown that BRD9 and

509
00:30:27.584 --> 00:30:31.364
non-canonical BAF maintain this differentiation block and

510
00:30:31.444 --> 00:30:34.364
maintain the stemness of these myeloid precursors.

511
00:30:34.394 --> 00:30:37.944
And targeting that BRD9 removes that

512
00:30:38.004 --> 00:30:41.624
differentiation block and imparts a survival

513
00:30:41.704 --> 00:30:44.504
advantage in models of AML and

514
00:30:44.884 --> 00:30:47.544
induces morphological differentiation.

515
00:30:47.914 --> 00:30:51.744
And for this reason, we chose to target BRD9 as a potential

516
00:30:51.784 --> 00:30:54.084
broad-acting inducer of differentiation.

517
00:30:55.844 --> 00:30:59.694
Now, the degraders which we've used to target this protein are slightly

518
00:30:59.744 --> 00:31:03.584
different than the more familiar PROTACs that may be known to

519
00:31:03.624 --> 00:31:07.404
you, which generally engage the E3 ligases

520
00:31:07.444 --> 00:31:10.864
cereblon and VHL. Our compounds bind

521
00:31:10.984 --> 00:31:13.674
only to the target protein initially,

522
00:31:14.544 --> 00:31:18.164
in this case, BRD9. Only once bound to the target protein do they

523
00:31:18.204 --> 00:31:21.624
engage the E3 ligase machinery. In this case, it's

524
00:31:21.684 --> 00:31:22.804
DCAP16.

525
00:31:23.744 --> 00:31:25.924
And once the ternary complex is formed,

526
00:31:26.384 --> 00:31:30.044
the degrader forms

527
00:31:30.104 --> 00:31:33.964
a covalent but reversible bond with the E3

528
00:31:34.004 --> 00:31:37.024
ligase. This stabilizes the ternary complex,

529
00:31:38.164 --> 00:31:42.124
allows the target to be ubiquitinated, and directed to

530
00:31:42.164 --> 00:31:44.554
the proteasomal degradation machinery.

531
00:31:45.184 --> 00:31:48.604
Our compounds have no or very little affinity for the E3

532
00:31:48.684 --> 00:31:51.384
ligase in the absence of the target protein.

533
00:31:52.884 --> 00:31:55.424
So the design of our libraries is modular.

534
00:31:55.604 --> 00:31:59.264
We identify a selection of high-affinity binders to

535
00:31:59.324 --> 00:32:01.784
the target protein, BRD9 in this case.

536
00:32:02.164 --> 00:32:05.824
We have a whole variety of linkers

537
00:32:06.084 --> 00:32:09.244
offering different vectors, different geometries, and different proteins,

538
00:32:09.924 --> 00:32:13.474
different properties. And we have a range of

539
00:32:13.504 --> 00:32:16.884
warheads offering, again, different properties and different geometries.

540
00:32:17.244 --> 00:32:21.064
The warhead I'll talk about in the talk today is based on this

541
00:32:21.104 --> 00:32:24.794
electrophilic warhead, the cyanoacrylamide, but we do have

542
00:32:24.844 --> 00:32:28.664
other warheads that we employ. The library resulted after

543
00:32:28.724 --> 00:32:32.544
some optimization in the compound shown in the middle there, which is already a

544
00:32:32.584 --> 00:32:36.124
potent compound, a DC50 sub-nanomolar, and very

545
00:32:36.204 --> 00:32:39.544
selective against related BRD proteins.

546
00:32:39.984 --> 00:32:43.684
And we've shown that it does degrade by DCAP16.

547
00:32:44.744 --> 00:32:48.224
The optimization of this molecule focused on increasing the speed of degradation,

548
00:32:48.284 --> 00:32:51.854
which is something we found empirically to be important to elicit the biology,

549
00:32:52.364 --> 00:32:55.904
optimizing the pharmacokinetics, and by that I mean really optimizing the

550
00:32:55.944 --> 00:32:58.984
metabolism of the compound, all whilst maintaining the

551
00:32:59.024 --> 00:33:02.704
selectivity. And this resulted in AMX883,

552
00:33:02.944 --> 00:33:04.324
which is our clinical candidate,

553
00:33:05.144 --> 00:33:09.124
a very potent compound. I'd just like to emphasize we're quoting the DC90 here,

554
00:33:09.284 --> 00:33:12.924
the DC90 of 0.3 nanomolar. Very potent compound,

555
00:33:13.164 --> 00:33:17.084
very selective against related proteins, orally bioavailable in every

556
00:33:17.164 --> 00:33:19.904
species we tested it in. And very gratifying,

557
00:33:20.884 --> 00:33:24.744
we were able to isolate this as a solid

558
00:33:24.864 --> 00:33:28.724
form, a salt form, a solid form, crystalline, which we were able

559
00:33:28.764 --> 00:33:31.504
to formulate for dosing in the clinic.

560
00:33:33.944 --> 00:33:37.784
I've said much of this already. A very potent selective degrader, a very

561
00:33:37.824 --> 00:33:41.224
fast degrader, and importantly for the disease

562
00:33:41.304 --> 00:33:45.104
context, it degrades across a panel of AML

563
00:33:45.344 --> 00:33:46.124
cell lines.

564
00:33:47.164 --> 00:33:50.844
BRD9 is the only protein that AMX883

565
00:33:51.004 --> 00:33:54.654
degrades, and the proteomics experiment on the left-hand side there,

566
00:33:55.144 --> 00:33:57.184
the protein which looks like it might be

567
00:33:57.264 --> 00:34:01.144
approaching significance is actually

568
00:34:01.184 --> 00:34:04.484
MYB, M-Y-B, hematopoietic transcription factor.

569
00:34:04.544 --> 00:34:08.104
We believe that's downstream of BRD9 degradation.

570
00:34:09.205 --> 00:34:13.124
As evidence that the degradation is mediated by

571
00:34:14.564 --> 00:34:18.524
the proteasome and the cullin-RING E3 ligase, we see

572
00:34:18.564 --> 00:34:22.484
no degradation in the presence of the proteasome inhibitor bortezomib

573
00:34:22.784 --> 00:34:25.745
or the neddylation inhibitor MLN4924.

574
00:34:26.984 --> 00:34:30.904
As evidence that DCAP16 is the mechanism of action,

575
00:34:31.034 --> 00:34:33.593
we see no degradation when we knock out DCAP16.

576
00:34:34.225 --> 00:34:37.644
When we reintroduce DCAP16, we see degradation.

577
00:34:37.665 --> 00:34:41.324
But when we reintroduce DCAP16 with a cysteine

578
00:34:41.334 --> 00:34:44.915
mutation, cysteine 58 is mutated, we see no degradation,

579
00:34:45.424 --> 00:34:49.245
suggesting that it is that cysteine that binds

580
00:34:49.765 --> 00:34:52.745
to our cyanoacrylamide motif.

581
00:34:53.804 --> 00:34:57.484
We were able to generate a cryo-EM structure of the

582
00:34:57.524 --> 00:35:01.124
ternary complex of AMX883 bound to BRD9 and

583
00:35:01.204 --> 00:35:01.964
DCAP16.

584
00:35:03.004 --> 00:35:06.804
This confirms that it is indeed cysteine 58 which our compound

585
00:35:06.864 --> 00:35:10.214
reacts with. But this also revealed

586
00:35:10.244 --> 00:35:14.000
several-True glue-like interactions that

587
00:35:14.060 --> 00:35:17.480
AMX883 is inducing in this ternary

588
00:35:17.620 --> 00:35:18.359
complex.

589
00:35:21.400 --> 00:35:25.180
Now, there's no single marker of differentiation,

590
00:35:25.300 --> 00:35:29.280
so we use a panel of markers. Sorry, I'm a bit close to that.

591
00:35:29.840 --> 00:35:33.300
A panel of markers to measure differentiation

592
00:35:33.340 --> 00:35:37.260
across this panel of cell lines. I have to

593
00:35:37.300 --> 00:35:40.560
say that this panel of markers is probably skewed to myeloid

594
00:35:40.600 --> 00:35:43.700
differentiation. The first thing to note is that

595
00:35:44.000 --> 00:35:47.280
AMX883 has broad activity across this cell panel,

596
00:35:48.400 --> 00:35:51.040
but also you have to degrade this protein.

597
00:35:51.460 --> 00:35:55.080
The inhibitor does not induce differentiation, so this is a

598
00:35:55.140 --> 00:35:58.940
target that has to be degraded. And on the right-hand

599
00:35:59.060 --> 00:36:02.680
side, we can show comparable degradation,

600
00:36:03.000 --> 00:36:05.880
sorry, comparable differentiation induction

601
00:36:07.580 --> 00:36:11.480
to the many inhibitors in cell lines which would be expected to be

602
00:36:11.540 --> 00:36:13.900
sensitive to many inhibitors.

603
00:36:17.260 --> 00:36:17.380
Now,

604
00:36:18.500 --> 00:36:21.500
BRD9 and the non-canonical BAF are

605
00:36:21.740 --> 00:36:24.380
involved in chromatin remodeling.

606
00:36:25.140 --> 00:36:26.600
Of course, this involves

607
00:36:27.600 --> 00:36:31.440
changing the accessibility of the chromatin and allowing transcription

608
00:36:31.480 --> 00:36:35.290
of genes. So we ran a time course ATAC-seq experiment.

609
00:36:36.000 --> 00:36:39.730
First thing to notice is that the initial changes are all about

610
00:36:40.120 --> 00:36:44.100
loss of accessibility. And that loss of accessibility occurs

611
00:36:44.140 --> 00:36:44.260
in

612
00:36:45.120 --> 00:36:49.100
regions enriched for binding sites to hematopoietic

613
00:36:49.110 --> 00:36:52.780
transcription factors, notably MIB, which I've already

614
00:36:52.840 --> 00:36:55.290
mentioned, RUNX, CBP1, PU1.

615
00:36:56.620 --> 00:37:00.520
That's followed in later time points by reduction of accessibility

616
00:37:00.580 --> 00:37:04.280
to other hematopoietic transcription factor binding

617
00:37:04.360 --> 00:37:07.960
sites. There is no initial increase,

618
00:37:08.440 --> 00:37:09.840
gain of accessibility,

619
00:37:10.800 --> 00:37:13.520
across any of these sites in the first six hours.

620
00:37:13.880 --> 00:37:17.590
Related time points, we do see gain of accessibility through a number of these

621
00:37:17.600 --> 00:37:20.580
hematopoietic transcription factors.

622
00:37:20.620 --> 00:37:24.420
When you look at the transcript level, you

623
00:37:24.520 --> 00:37:24.740
see

624
00:37:25.700 --> 00:37:28.820
an induction of gene sets associated with myeloid

625
00:37:28.880 --> 00:37:32.260
