resulting from these doses because, and I've seen this with other programs,

752
00:44:58.656 --> 00:45:01.996
you have these unbelievable subnanomolar compounds,

753
00:45:02.516 --> 00:45:06.316
but if the doses generate, say, micromolar

754
00:45:06.436 --> 00:45:07.216
concentrations,

755
00:45:08.056 --> 00:45:09.536
what's the benefit when it comes to-

756
00:45:09.576 --> 00:45:09.626
Yeah

757
00:45:09.676 --> 00:45:11.036
... efficacy versus toxicity?

758
00:45:11.436 --> 00:45:15.176
So the doses that we require to see efficacy in mouse

759
00:45:15.216 --> 00:45:17.276
models are determined by mouse PK.

760
00:45:17.556 --> 00:45:19.876
This is a high clearance compound in mouse PK.

761
00:45:21.136 --> 00:45:24.896
In terms of the concentrations required to see efficacy,

762
00:45:25.496 --> 00:45:29.276
we find that we need free concentrations exceeding the

763
00:45:29.295 --> 00:45:32.536
DC90, so it's nanomolar. We need nanomolar

764
00:45:32.576 --> 00:45:34.596
concentrations of this to see efficacy.

765
00:45:35.476 --> 00:45:35.836
Thank you.

766
00:45:39.116 --> 00:45:40.296
Great talk. Thank you.

767
00:45:42.176 --> 00:45:42.876
My question was,

